USA: Repetition is the mother of wisdom
It is comical that Barack Obama, the president with the reputation of the smartest man, as a diligent student repeats in the Afghan question the strategy of his predecessor, whom he himself took for the most foolish.
When he finally revealed his Afghan approach, eagerly awaited, it was shown to be a copy of the script used for Iraq by Bush, created three years ago.
Not only in the same text is the word "equal to Iraq" used several times, but it did not hesitate to use the title of the January 2007 Bush declaration for its own statement: "A new way forward."
It was himself, who three years ago criticized Bush's idea of sending new military reinforcements to Iraq, the country that is suffering from civil war, and that criticized him as "an irresponsible decision with catastrophic consequences."
The following months, however, showed that Bush's strategy, based on recommendations from field captains, was the only possible and successful, so that nothing is talked about today about Iraq in the news.
Bush's reputation did not improve, however objectively left his successor a much more favorable initial situation than he could expect.
In Afghanistan, Barack Obama expects the miracle to be repeated.
The camp captains again asked him to increase the military contingent, especially the commander-in-chief of the general Afghan operation Stanley McCristal. He, even in spite of the traditional subordinate relations, submitted to the undecided gunmen in the White House a harsh criticism.
He asked 40,000 men to be able to improve the situation.
The president hesitated for three months, but nothing better happened to him, so at least he cheated the general over 10,000 soldiers.
He managed to get Europe to promise him a further 5,000, although he himself previously had at least 10,000.
The most problematic thing about Obama's entire strategy seems to be his goal, to start withdrawing Afghanistan's troops in 18 months, and to finish this procedure in three years. All Obama's doctrine generated more questions from the answers he offered.
Many doubt that the increase bears the same fruit as the procedure in Iraq.
Despite the fratricidal wars in recent years, Iraq's society is relatively well organized, its leaders respect the agreements.
The situation in Afghanistan is different: no one can be trusted and no agreement is reached.
Under these conditions it is difficult to prepare the Afghan security forces, if they are accustomed to changing the boss every day according to their needs.
Political institutions, although formally established, will remain only a people of Potemkin. After him, patriarchal tribal relations will remain.
Balancing the interests of different ethnic groups is extraordinarily complicated because of confused relations, even more complicated by Pakistani and Iranian influences.
Not even establishing a state that is "capable of action", a minimum goal of the entire operation, seems very real.
The horizon of Obama's strategy is shocking at his volunteerism.
For the past eight years, the situation in Afghanistan has continued to worsen and is now about to explode.
Only a romantic soul, who knows nothing about reality, can believe that the military sent to the war to "come home soon," will do some miracle here.
From a political point of view, setting the date of withdrawal of troops is purely irresponsible, as the Taliban will consider it an indirect declaration of the US defeat.
The latest NATO summit showed that Europeans are increasingly less willing to participate in military operations in Afghanistan.
European politicians don't know, and they don't want to explain to their constituents, what the security of Germany or Italy has to do with the war with Hindu Kush.
The other factor, which can radically affect the situation, is the development of developments in Iran.
If the situation continues to worsen and increased sanctions have no effect on Iranians, the United States will have to make a difficult decision: to try to solve the problem with military force or not.
It will be necessary to look for answers precisely when, according to Obama, America initiates the triumphal withdrawal of Afghanistan's troops.
However, each solution will mean a dramatic setback for the Afghan situation.
The only positive point for Barack Obama is that it is three years away for the presidential elections and so there is still a lot of time left to find another strategy, if this is a total failure.
