As happened with ABS brake antilock and will pass with ESP stability control, emergency braking aid systems will have to be a mandatory element in European cars.
In fact, this is already the case in all new-registered light commercial vehicles and tourism, while for the rest a shortage period is fixed until the end of February 2011.
The measure, imposed by the European Union, aims to increase the protection of pedestrians, although it can also help to avoid many collisions by scope.
The emergency brake assistant is to increase the pressure on the brakes in the event of an emergency, which the system detects by the driver's pedestrian.
But this does not always hold that pressure until the end.
